# LICENCE — docs/

This folder contains the documentation layer for `iontrap-structure`. The
package source under `src/` and `tests/` is **MIT** (see the repository-root
[`LICENSE`](https://github.com/uwarring82/iontrap-structure/blob/main/LICENSE));
the documentation here is licensed separately, mirroring the split used by the
sibling project `iontrap-dynamics`.

## Licence split inside `docs/`

- **Coastline material** in the `docs/` root — `index.md`, `overview.md`,
  `getting-started.md`, `conventions.md`, `validation.md`, `api.md`, and any
  future top-level `.md` — is licensed under **CC BY-SA 4.0**
  (`CC-BY-SA-4.0`).
- **Sail material** under `docs/tutorials/` — the tutorials and their generated
  Colab notebooks — is licensed under **CC BY-NC-SA 4.0**
  (`CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0`).

The distinction follows the sibling's convention: Coastline material states
binding constraints (conventions, scope, API); Sail material is adaptive
guidance with specific worked parameter choices.

## Stylesheets

- `stylesheets/tokens.css` — design tokens, **MIT**, vendored upstream
  (see the in-file header). Mirrored from `iontrap-dynamics` for visual
  consistency across the sibling pair.
- `stylesheets/extra.css` — site-local styling, **CC BY-SA 4.0**. Mirrored from
  `iontrap-dynamics`, where it originates; both repositories are maintained by
  the same author.

## Generated notebooks

`docs/tutorials/notebooks/*.ipynb` are a **derived artifact** generated from the
Markdown tutorials by `tools/build_tutorial_notebooks.py`. They carry the same
**CC BY-NC-SA 4.0** licence as the tutorials they are built from.

## Precedence

If an individual file inside `docs/` declares a different SPDX identifier, that
file-level declaration takes precedence over this folder-level default.

## Endorsement Marker

Local candidate framework under active stewardship. No external endorsement is
implied.
